Configuring the command prompt to show us the branch:

__git_ps1
// it will return the name of the current branch

How to configure prompt in Unix:
echo $PS1

Example:
export PS1='----->'
----------------
export PS1='\W$(__git_ps1 "(%s)") > '

cd ~

nano .bash_profile

export PS1='\W$(__git_ps1 "(%s)") > '

In widnows Do the same thing by creating a .bash_profile file inside the "User directory" and then the following command:

source ~/.bash_profile
